county_name:  state: PA  headline: Winter Weather Advisory until TUE 1:00 PM EST  county_fips:  category: Met  url:  urgency: Expected  severity: Moderate  certainty: Likely  geographicname: Lehigh County  state_name: Pennsylvania        Reporter        BETHLEHEM, Pa - Fans of a former Bethlehem Catholic and Lehigh University standout are gathered at an area restaurant Thursday morning as they cheer for him at\\u00a0the Olympic Games in Paris.  They watched as Darian Cruz was able to get a pin against Egypt during round one and advance to the quarter-finals. In his second match, Cruz fell to Japan.  Cruz is representing his grandparents' native Puerto Rico when competing in the men's freestyle 57 kg wrestling division.  WATCH: 69 News was live as fans watched Cruz advance to the quarter-finals.  Cruz won the first match\\u00a0at 57 kg by pinning Egypt's Gamal Mohamed in 2:30, 4-1.  In the quarters, Cruz fell 12-2 to top seed at 57 kg,\\u00a0Rei Higuchi.  Higuchi of Japan advanced the finals in a Thursday afternoon match. He goes to the finals on Friday.  With\\u00a0Higuchi's win, Cruz gets pulled back in. He has a shot at the bronze medal on Friday.  Cruz will compete against Aman Sehrawat of India., who lost to\\u00a0Higuchi on Thursday.  69 News reporter Priscilla Liguori caught up with wrestler Darian Cruz ahead of his trip to the Olympics in Paris.  Cruz won two PIAA Class 2A individual wrestling titles at Bethlehem Catholic in 2012 and 2013 and a NCAA Division I national title at Lehigh University in 2017.  Anthony Spagnola, owner of Sotto Santi Pizzeria Pub in south Bethlehem, organized the Olympics watch party for Cruz.  The watch party included a $10 all-you-can-eat buffet, featuring breakfast selections such as quiches, breakfast pizza, assorted muffins, fresh fruit, coffee and orange juice.  Stick with 69 News for updates.  Former Bethlehem Catholic and Lehigh University standout, Darian Cruz is looking to add to his long list of accolades in Paris. Cruz is set to compete for team Puerto Rico on the mat during the Summer Games.  Reporter      Get local Breaking News alerts sent directly to your inbox.  Success!An email has been sent towith a link to confirm list signup.  Error!There was an error processing your request.  Watch all of WFMZ-TV News and Syndicated Programing 24/7 on your Streaming App enabled TV.  Your browser is out of date and potentially vulnerable to security risks.We recommend switching to one of the following browsers:  Get up-to-the-minute news sent straight to your device.\"}"